name: Card
desc:
Enum for cards and their basic methods.
(see Card @ wiki)

name: compareTo
desc: Compares this object to another object.

name: fromInt
desc: Create one from integer value

name: fromRankSuit
desc: Create one from rank and suit

name: fromText
desc: Create one from text representation

name: fullName
desc: Full English name

name: highAceFix
desc: Make low aces high, leave other cards alone

name: highRank
desc: What's the rank of this card, with low aces made high?

name: isAce
desc: Is this card an ace?

name: isBlack
desc:
Is this card black? Note that while jokers have no suit, there is a
black one and a red one.

name: isCard
desc: Is this an actual card (and not None or an invalid number)?

name: isJoker
desc: Is this card a joker?

name: isRed
desc:
Is this card red? Note that while jokers have no suit, there is a
black one and a red one.

name: lowAceFix
desc: Make high aces low, leave other cards alone

name: rank
desc:
What's the rank of this card? Note that we use a shift on the number
value; that's why the numbers are important. Note that jokers do not
have rank or suit.

name: suit
desc: What's the suit of this card?

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: toText
desc: Render to two-character text in standard format

name: toUnicode
desc: Render to two-character text with unicode suit symbols

name: toUnicodeSingle
desc: Render to single-character unicode card image.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: Deck
desc: A "live" Deck of cards that is used for a game.

name: Deck
desc: Create a new Deck from a MasterDeck name

name: clearAll
desc: Clear all associated Hands.

name: combinations
desc:
Iterate over all distinct count-sized Hands from the remaining deck.
For this purpose, hands with the same cards in different order are
considered "distinct". For example, on a fresh 52-card deck,
for h in d.combinations(5) will iterate over all 2598960 5-card hands.

name: contains
desc: Does the Deck contain the given Card?

name: dealAll
desc:
Deal all Hands created from this deck a number of cards. Useful at
the start of a hand of play, e.g. d.dealAll(5);.

name: dealTo
desc: Deal a single card to the given Hand

name: hands
desc: Hands spawned from this deck

name: isEmpty
desc: Have all Cards been dealt?

name: isNotEmpty
desc: Are any Cards remaining?

name: iterator
desc: Implementation of iterator

name: length
desc: How many Cards remain?

name: master
desc: Associated MasterDeck from which to fill this one

name: pop
desc:
Pop a Card from the Deck. This is expected to be the primary way
cards are taken (the dealXX functions call this).

name: popN
desc: Pop a number of Cards from the Deck.

name: push
desc: Add a Card to the Deck. Not expected to be used often.

name: pushN
desc: Push a number of Cards back onto the Deck.

name: refill
desc: Refill the Deck from its associated MasterDeck.

name: remaining
desc: Synonym for "length"

name: removeCard
desc:
Remove a specific Card from the Deck by its identity.
(e.g. d.removeCard(Card.JackOfClubs)).

name: shuffle
desc: Randomize the Cards remaining in the Deck.

name: size
desc: How many cards in full deck?

name: sort
desc:
Sort the Deck into the same descending order by Rank and Suit as
used for Hands. Note that this will make the deck appear to be in the
reverse ascending order when printed (see toString(), below).

name: toList
desc: Copy the remaining Cards onto a new List.

name: toString
desc:
Print contents of Deck. Note that for performance, cards are popped
from the end of the list, which makes it the notional "top" of the deck.
For testing and simulation purposes, deck contents are shown backwards:
i.e., from the end of the list to the front.

name: validCard
desc:
Validate that the Card passed is legal for this deck.
Convert high and low aces if necessary.

name: aceFix
desc: Fix cards for decks with low/high aces.

name: removeCard
desc: Remove top-most specific card from list.

name: shuffle
desc: Randomize order of cards in the stack.

name: sort
desc: Sort cards in the stack in descending order from the top.

name: next32
desc:
Generate a random 32-bit integer. While Dart uses 64-bit integers,
it can be compiled into JavaScript, which doesn't play nice with
64-bit ints, so we stick to 32 here.

name: rangeUniform
desc:
Return a random integer uniformly distributed in the range [0, limit)
with no division, using rejection sampling. The mask m is used to
minimize rejections, which will be at worst 50%.
